<i>adverb</i>: 훌렁 [훌렁], 훌러덩 [훌러덩], 호락호락 [호라코락], 폭삭 [폭싹], 편히 [편히], 편안히 [펴난히], 툭하면 [투카면], 툭툭 [툭툭], 툭 [툭], 턱턱 [턱턱], 탁탁 [탁탁], 척척 [척척], 착착 [착착], 줄줄 [줄줄], 좀체 [좀ː체], 좀처럼 [좀ː처럼], 족히 [조키], 예사로 [예ː사로], 쑥 [쑥], 쏙쏙 [쏙쏙], 쏙 [쏙], 슬쩍슬쩍 [슬쩍쓸쩍], 슬쩍 [슬쩍], 쉬이 [쉬이], 쉬 [쉬ː], 술술 [술술], 수월히 [수월히], 솔솔 [솔솔], 살짝 [살짝], 번쩍 [번쩍], 반짝 [반짝], 문제없이 [문ː제업씨], 무난히 [무난히], 만만히 [만만히], 막힘없이 [마키멉씨], 뚝딱뚝딱 [뚝딱뚝딱], 뚝딱 [뚝딱], 너끈히 [너끈히], 까딱하면 [까따카면], 걸핏하면 [걸피타면], 간단히 [간단히], 가뿐히 [가뿐히], 가벼이 [가벼이], 가뜬히 [가뜬히] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>훌렁 [훌렁]</dt><br>
<dd>1. completely; thoroughly</dd><br>
<dd>속이 시원하게 드러나도록 완전히 벗어지거나 뒤집히는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the motion of something being completely taken off or turned inside out so that the inside is clearly exposed.</dd><br>
<dd>2. completely; thoroughly</dd><br>
<dd>가지고 있던 돈이나 재산 등을 다 날려 버리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of losing all of one's money or wealth, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>3. loosely; in a slippery manner</dd><br>
<dd>구멍이 넓어서 아주 헐겁게 빠지거나 들어가는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the manner of slipping out easily or fitting loosely because the hole is wide.</dd><br>
<dd>4. easily; effortlessly</dd><br>
<dd>아주 쉽게 뛰어넘거나 들어 올리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the motion of jumping across or lifting something very easily.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>훌러덩 [훌러덩]</dt><br>
<dd>1. completely; thoroughly</dd><br>
<dd>속이 시원하게 드러나도록 완전히 벗어지거나 뒤집히는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the motion of something being completely taken off or turned inside out so that the inside is clearly exposed.</dd><br>
<dd>2. completely; thoroughly</dd><br>
<dd>가지고 있던 돈이나 재산 등을 다 날려 버리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of losing all of one's money or wealth, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>3. easily; effortlessly</dd><br>
<dd>아주 쉽게 뛰어넘거나 들어 올리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the motion of jumping across or lifting something very easily.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>호락호락 [호라코락]</dt><br>
<dd>easily; without difficulty; effortlessly</dd><br>
<dd>일이나 사람이 만만하여 다루기 쉬운 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a task or person being pliable enough to be easily managed.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>폭삭 [폭싹]</dt><br>
<dd>1. completely; easily</dd><br>
<dd>매우 엉성한 물건이 부드럽게 가라앉거나 쉽게 부서지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing an act of a very flimsy object smoothly collapsing or being broken easily.</dd><br>
<dd>2. heavily</dd><br>
<dd>기운이 없이 주저앉는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one's act of sitting down heavily due to feeling weak.</dd><br>
<dd>3. lightly</dd><br>
<dd>쌓였던 먼지 등이 갑자기 가볍게 일어나는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of stacked dust, etc., rising suddenly and lightly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. completely</dd><br>
<dd>심하게 삭거나 썩은 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of something being severely fermented or rotten.</dd><br>
<dd>5. completely</dd><br>
<dd>힘이 약해지고 늙어 버린 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of someone becoming weak and old.</dd><br>
<dd>6. rapidly</dd><br>
<dd>기운이 아주 꺼져 들어가는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of one's energy diminishing greatly.</dd><br>
<dd>7. all at once</dd><br>
<dd>담겼던 물건이 한꺼번에 쏟아지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of contained objects being spilled all at once.</dd><br>
<dd>8. completely</dd><br>
<dd>집안이 완전히 망해 버린 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of a family going completely bankrupt or being ruined.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>편히 [편히]</dt><br>
<dd>comfortably; easily</dd><br>
<dd>몸이나 마음이 괴롭지 않고 좋게.</dd><br>
<dd>Nicely without any trouble for one's body or mind.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>편안히 [펴난히]</dt><br>
<dd>comfortably; easily</dd><br>
<dd>몸이나 마음이 편하고 좋은 상태로.</dd><br>
<dd>In a relaxed and good condition in one's body or mind.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>툭하면 [투카면]</dt><br>
<dd>easily; readily</dd><br>
<dd>조금이라도 일이나 기회가 있기만 하면 바로.</dd><br>
<dd>Immediately at the slightest provocation.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>툭툭 [툭툭]</dt><br>
<dd>1. pop-pop</dd><br>
<dd>자꾸 튀거나 터지는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when something suddenly keeps popping up or bursting open, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>2. with a thump</dd><br>
<dd>자꾸 떨어지는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when something suddenly keeps falling down, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>3. bluntly</dd><br>
<dd>무뚝뚝하거나 못마땅한 말투로 자꾸 말하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing someone who keeps talking bluntly or disapprovingly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. in one’s way</dd><br>
<dd>발에 자꾸 걸리거나 차이는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when something keeps getting in someone's way or getting kicked, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>5. tap-tap</dd><br>
<dd>자꾸 가볍게 치거나 건드리는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when one gently keeps tapping or touching something, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>6. gently</dd><br>
<dd>자꾸 가볍게 털거나 튀기는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when one gently keeps shaking or bouncing something, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>7. simply; easily</dd><br>
<dd>갑자기 자꾸 부러지거나 끊어지는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when something suddenly keeps breaking suddenly and easily, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>8. bulgingly</dd><br>
<dd>여기저기 둥글게 내밀어 나온 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing several parts of something protruding here and there.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>툭 [툭]</dt><br>
<dd>1. pop</dd><br>
<dd>갑자기 튀거나 터지는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when something suddenly pops up or bursts open, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>2. with a thump</dd><br>
<dd>갑자기 떨어지는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when something suddenly falls down, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>3. bluntly</dd><br>
<dd>무뚝뚝하거나 못마땅한 말투로 불쑥 말하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when one talks bluntly or disapprovingly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. in one’s way</dd><br>
<dd>갑자기 발에 걸리거나 차이는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when something gets in someone's way or gets kicked, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>5. tap-tap; gently</dd><br>
<dd>가볍게 치거나 건드리는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when one gently taps or touches something, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>6. gently</dd><br>
<dd>가볍게 털거나 튀기는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when one gently shakes or bounces something, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>7. simply; easily</dd><br>
<dd>갑자기 부러지거나 끊어지는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when something suddenly breaks suddenly and easily, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>8. bulgingly</dd><br>
<dd>어느 한 부분이 둥글게 내밀어 나온 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a part of something protruding.</dd><br>
<dd>9. openly</dd><br>
<dd>환하게 트이거나 숨기는 것 없이 터놓는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a place with an open view, or someone speaking frankly.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>턱턱 [턱턱]</dt><br>
<dd>1. easily</dd><br>
<dd>일을 매우 시원스럽고 의젓하게 처리하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one’s handling a task in a very brisk and mature manner.</dd><br>
<dd>2. completely</dd><br>
<dd>숨 등이 계속 몹시 막히는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one's sudden and repeated state of being short of breath, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>3. spit-spit</dd><br>
<dd>침을 계속 세게 뱉는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when one spits out repeatedly and strongly, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>4. with a thump</dd><br>
<dd>계속 세게 쓰러지거나 거꾸러지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one's act of falling down or tumbling down repeatedly and heavily.</dd><br>
<dd>5. abruptly</dd><br>
<dd>갑자기 자꾸 멈춰 버리거나 무엇에 걸리는 모양. 또는 그 소리.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing something suddenly and repeatedly stopping or being stuck in an object, or imitating such a sound.</dd><br>
<dd>6. with a thump</dd><br>
<dd>무엇을 자꾸 세게 치거나 먼지 등을 터는 소리. 또는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when something is repeatedly and strongly beaten or dusted, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>7. with a pop</dd><br>
<dd>튼튼한 물건이 갑자기 세게 터지며 나는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when a strong object suddenly bursts, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>8. in a snap</dd><br>
<dd>갑자기 아주 힘없이 잘리거나 끊어져 계속 나는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound repeatedly made when an object is cut or snapped suddenly and helplessly, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>탁탁 [탁탁]</dt><br>
<dd>1. easily</dd><br>
<dd>의젓하거나 태연스럽게 일을 처리하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state in which one handles a task in a mature and calm manner.</dd><br>
<dd>2. with a thump</dd><br>
<dd>사람이나 물건이 계속 쓰러지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state in which a person or object keeps falling.</dd><br>
<dd>3. completely</dd><br>
<dd>숨 등이 계속 막히는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state in which one is continuously short of breath.</dd><br>
<dd>4. spit-spit</dd><br>
<dd>침을 계속 뱉는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when one spits out strongly, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>5. with a thump</dd><br>
<dd>단단한 물건을 자꾸 두드리거나 먼지 등을 터는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when one keeps hitting a hard object or beating dust off something, etc., or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>6. with a pop</dd><br>
<dd>단단한 물건이 갑자기 터져 계속 나는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when a hard object suddenly bursts, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>7. in a snap</dd><br>
<dd>물건이 아주 힘없이 잘리거나 끊어져 계속 나는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when an object is cut or snapped repeatedly, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>척척 [척척]</dt><br>
<dd>1. quickly without hesitation</dd><br>
<dd>전혀 망설이지 않고 선뜻선뜻 행동하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of doing a certain act swiftly and without hesitation.</dd><br>
<dd>2. easily</dd><br>
<dd>일이 막힘이 없이 아주 잘되어 가는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of something going smoothly without any problems.</dd><br>
<dd>3. steadily</dd><br>
<dd>질서 있게 조화를 이루어 행동하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In an orderly and systematic fashion.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>착착 [착착]</dt><br>
<dd>1. quickly without hesitation</dd><br>
<dd>망설이지 않고 빠르고 시원하게 행동하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the manner of doing a certain act swiftly, vigorously, and without hesitation.</dd><br>
<dd>2. easily</dd><br>
<dd>일이 막힘없이 잘되어 가는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of something going smoothly without any problems.</dd><br>
<dd>3. steadily</dd><br>
<dd>조화를 이루어 질서 있게 행동하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In an orderly and systematic fashion.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>줄줄 [줄줄]</dt><br>
<dd>1. continuously</dd><br>
<dd>굵은 물줄기 등이 계속 흐르는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>With a sound resembling one that is produced when a thick flow of water, etc., keeps running, or such a shape.</dd><br>
<dd>2. continuously</dd><br>
<dd>동물이나 사람이 자꾸 뒤를 따르거나 쫓아다니는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that an animal or human keeps following another around.</dd><br>
<dd>3. all over the place</dd><br>
<dd>물건을 여기저기 자꾸 흘리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that one keeps spilling objects here and there.</dd><br>
<dd>4. without stopping</dd><br>
<dd>조금도 막힘이 없이 읽거나 외우거나 말하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that one reads, recites or speaks without faltering a bit.</dd><br>
<dd>5. easily</dd><br>
<dd>물건 등이 자꾸 미끄러지거나 흘러내리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that an object, etc., keeps sliding or running down.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>좀체 [좀ː체]</dt><br>
<dd>easily; anytime soon</dd><br>
<dd>이만저만하거나 어지간해서는.</dd><br>
<dd>In usual or ordinary circumstances.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>좀처럼 [좀ː처럼]</dt><br>
<dd>easily; anytime soon</dd><br>
<dd>이만저만하거나 어지간해서는.</dd><br>
<dd>In usual or ordinary circumstances.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>족히 [조키]</dt><br>
<dd>1. at least</dd><br>
<dd>수나 양, 정도 등이 넉넉하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being sufficient in number, quantity, degree, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>2. fully; easily</dd><br>
<dd>모자람이 없어서 더 바라는 바가 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being fully satisfactory with nothing lacking.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>예사로 [예ː사로]</dt><br>
<dd>1. usually; easily</dd><br>
<dd>보통 일처럼 아무렇지도 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of making nothing of doing something as if it was nothing special.</dd><br>
<dd>2. as an ordinary thing</dd><br>
<dd>그저 그만하게.</dd><br>
<dd>As a common thing.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>쑥 [쑥]</dt><br>
<dd>1. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>안으로 깊이 들어가거나 밖으로 불룩하게 내미는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the motion of something sinking in deeply or shooting out so that it protrudes.</dd><br>
<dd>2. easily</dd><br>
<dd>깊이 밀어 넣거나 길게 뽑아내는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the motion of pushing in something deeply or pulling out something long.</dd><br>
<dd>3. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>바로 빠지거나 터지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the motion of something falling out or bursting in an instant.</dd><br>
<dd>4. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>기운이나 살이 급격히 줄어드는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of one's energy or weight being lost.</dd><br>
<dd>5. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이나 집단에서 포함되지 않는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being excluded from something or a group.</dd><br>
<dd>6. cleanly; clearly</dd><br>
<dd>때가 깨끗이 없어지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of dirt being washed completely..</dd><br>
<dd>7. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>함부로 말하며 나서는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of intruding while talking carelessly.</dd><br>
<dd>8. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>겉모습이 매끈하게 좋은 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of having a sleek appearance.</dd><br>
<dd>9. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>갑자기 정신이 확 나가는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of becoming disoriented suddenly.</dd><br>
<dd>10. suddenly</dd><br>
<dd>갑자기 올라가거나 내려가는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of going up or down suddenly.</dd><br>
<dd>11. suddenly; unexpectedly</dd><br>
<dd>앞으로 나아가거나 갑자기 앞에 나타나는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of going forward or appearing in front of someone suddenly.</dd><br>
